data.title: Short Take: Silicon Graphics subsidiary purchased
data.meta_description: The Minnesota Supercomputer Center (MSCI), formerly owned by Silicon Graphics subsidiary Cray Research, has been purchased by Network Computing Services, a corporation held by three MSCI executives. Terms of the purchase were not disclosed; no layoffs are expected.
